### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Leather E-Commerce — API Tests
### Usage: Open in VS Code with the "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client)
###        Hit "Send Request" above any request to run it.
###
### Workflow:
###   1. Run the Health check to confirm the server is up
###   2. Create a Category first (products need a category ID)
###   3. Copy the returned _id into @categoryId below
###   4. Create a Product and copy its slug into @productSlug
###   5. Run Cart and admin tests
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@baseUrl    = http://localhost:3000/api
@categoryId = 6a0edb02261d5b46c0d79416
@productSlug = classic-bifold-wallet
@productId  = PASTE_PRODUCT_ID_HERE


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### HEALTH
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1. Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### CATEGORIES — Public
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2. Get all categories (empty on first run)
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories

###

### 3. Get category by slug — valid slug
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories/wallets

###

### 4. Get category by slug — should return 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories/this-does-not-exist


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### CATEGORIES — Admin (placeholder auth — passes through for now)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 5. Create category — valid
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Wallets",
  "slug": "wallets"
}

###

### 6. Create category — duplicate slug (should return Mongoose unique error)
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Wallets Duplicate",
  "slug": "wallets"
}

###

### 7. Create category — missing name (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "slug": "bags"
}

###

### 8. Create category — invalid slug format (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bags",
  "slug": "Bags With Spaces!!"
}

###

### 9. Create second category (copy its _id into @categoryId at the top)
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bags",
  "slug": "bags"
}

###

### 10. Update category — valid partial update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/categories/wallets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Premium Wallets"
}

###

### 11. Update category — slug that doesn't exist (should return 404)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/categories/non-existent-slug
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ghost"
}

###

### 12. Delete category — valid
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/categories/bags

###

### 13. Delete category — already deleted or never existed (should return 404)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/categories/bags


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### PRODUCTS — Public
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 14. Get all products — default pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/products

###

### 15. Get products — custom page and limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?page=1&limit=6

###

### 16. Get products — search by keyword
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?search=leather

###

### 17. Get products — filter by category ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?category={{categoryId}}

###

### 18. Get products — search + category combined
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?search=wallet&category={{categoryId}}

###

### 19. Get products — invalid page (should return 422)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?page=0

###

### 20. Get products — limit over 50 (should be capped or return 422)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?limit=999

###

### 21. Get products — invalid category ID format (should return 422)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?category=not-a-mongo-id

###

### 22. Get product by slug — valid (update @productSlug at the top first)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productSlug}}

###

### 23. Get product by slug — not found (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/this-product-does-not-exist


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### PRODUCTS — Admin
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 24. Create product — valid (paste a real categoryId at the top first)
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Classic Bifold Wallet",
  "slug": "classic-bifold-wallet",
  "description": "A slim, handcrafted genuine leather bifold wallet with 6 card slots.",
  "price": 49.99,
  "discountPrice": 39.99,
  "category": "{{categoryId}}",
  "stock": 100,
  "isFeatured": true,
  "images": [],
  "tags": ["wallet", "leather", "bifold", "slim"]
}

###

### 25. Create product — missing required fields (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Incomplete Product"
}

###

### 26. Create product — invalid slug format (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bad Slug",
  "slug": "Bad Slug With Capitals",
  "description": "Test",
  "price": 10,
  "category": "{{categoryId}}",
  "stock": 5
}

###

### 27. Create product — negative price (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Negative Price",
  "slug": "negative-price",
  "description": "Test",
  "price": -10,
  "category": "{{categoryId}}",
  "stock": 5
}

###

### 28. Create product — discount price higher than price (should return Mongoose error)
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bad Discount",
  "slug": "bad-discount",
  "description": "Test",
  "price": 20,
  "discountPrice": 50,
  "category": "{{categoryId}}",
  "stock": 5
}

###

### 29. Update product — valid partial update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productSlug}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 44.99,
  "stock": 80
}

###

### 30. Update product — not found (should return 404)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/products/ghost-product
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 10
}

###

### 31. Delete product — valid
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productSlug}}

###

### 32. Delete product — already deleted (should return 404)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productSlug}}


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### CART
### NOTE: Cart routes require auth (userId on req). These will return errors
###       until auth middleware is implemented. Tests are written ready for
###       when auth lands — add an Authorization header at that point.
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 33. Get cart
GET {{baseUrl}}/cart

###

### 34. Add item to cart — valid (use a real productId)
POST {{baseUrl}}/cart
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "quantity": 2
}

###

### 35. Add same item again — should increment quantity
POST {{baseUrl}}/cart
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "quantity": 1
}

###

### 36. Add to cart — invalid productId (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/cart
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "not-a-valid-mongo-id",
  "quantity": 1
}

###

### 37. Add to cart — quantity of 0 (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/cart
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "quantity": 0
}

###

### 38. Update cart item quantity
PUT {{baseUrl}}/cart/{{productId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "quantity": 5
}

###

### 39. Update cart item — invalid productId param (should return 422)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/cart/not-a-mongo-id
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "quantity": 3
}

###

### 40. Update cart item — quantity 0 (should return 422)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/cart/{{productId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "quantity": 0
}

###

### 41. Remove specific item from cart
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/cart/{{productId}}

###

### 42. Remove item — invalid productId (should return 422)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/cart/not-a-mongo-id

###

### 43. Clear entire cart
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/cart
